
Install DHCP Server in Ubuntu 16.04

1: Installing DHCP Server in Ubuntu by running the below command:

$ sudo apt install isc-dhcp-server

2: When the installation completes -> edit the file 

/etc/default/isc-dhcp-server



3:The main DHCP configuration file is /etc/dhcp/dhcpd.confa-> add all your network information to be sent to clients here.

4:Now, open and modify the main configuration file, define your DHCP server options by this command

$ sudo vi /etc/dhcp/dhcpd.conf

5:Now, define a subnetwork; here, weâ€™ll setup DHCP for 192.168.10.0/24 LAN network (use parameters that apply to your scenario).
